title: Olympus Range
text: Olympus Range () is a primarily ice-free <a href="mountain">mountain</a> range of <a href="Victoria%20Land">Victoria Land</a> with peaks over , between <a href="Victoria%20Valley">Victoria</a> and <a href="McKelvey%20Valley">McKelvey Valleys</a> on the north and <a href="Wright%20Valley">Wright Valley</a> on the south. Mapped by the <a href="Victoria%20University%20of%20Wellington%20Antarctic%20Expedition">Victoria University of Wellington Antarctic Expedition</a> (VUWAE), 1958–59, and named for the mythological home of the <a href="Greek%20gods">Greek gods</a>. Peaks in the range are named for figures in <a href="Greek%20mythology">Greek mythology</a>.
